NEW YORK — The Rays are looking to bounce back from Tuesday’s tough 2-0 loss to the Yankees tonight. The game features a matchup of two of the game’s top starters this season, the Rays’ Shane McClanahan and the Yankees’ Nestor Cortes. On Tuesday, the Rays made two errors that led to the two runs and failed to take advantage of two prime scoring opportunities. Here is the Rays’ lineup, with eight right-handed hitters, and thus no Ji-Man Choi, vs. Cortes: Also of note, the Rays have Isaac Paredes at first base for the first time in the majors, and Yandy Diaz at third rather than the other way around. Manager Kevin Cash said he felt Diaz was more comfortable at third, and that Paredes had been doing some work at first. And for the Yankees: • • • Sign up for the Rays Report weekly newsletter to get fresh perspectives on the Tampa Bay Rays and the rest of the majors from sports columnist John Romano. Never miss out on the latest with the Bucs, Rays, Lightning, Florida college sports and more. Follow our Tampa Bay Times sports team on Twitter and Facebook.